    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-21T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.9283/9–2151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Thailand</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-21T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 21, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>683. Dept approached by <gloss target="#t_BritEmb1">Brit Emb</gloss> with
                    suggestion US and UK Embs Bangkok make joint approach Thai Govt expressing
                    concern re reports that <gloss target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> troops in Shan State
                    area of Burma being supplied through Thailand with Amer arms; stating it appears
                    Burma Govt preparing formal protest to <gloss target="#t_SecyGenUN1">Secy Gen
                        UN</gloss> requesting <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> assistance in
                    stopping such flow of arms. Dept concurred with Brit suggestion and instructs
                    you in conjunction with Brit colleague make such approach requesting Thai Govt
                    coop in preventing any possible flow of arms through Thailand to <gloss
                        target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> troops in Shan States. Dept believes that
                    obvious effort made by Thai Govt to investigate and prevent any such smuggling
                    wld forestall possible embarrassment to Thai in <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss>
                </p>
                <p>Rptd info: Amembassy Rangoon 282; <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 150.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
